1 B. C. The members of the Board shall receive Twenty-two
2 Thousand Eight Hundred Dollars ($22,800.00) a salary of Eighty-five
3 Thousand Dollars ($85,000.00) per annum, payable monthly in the
4 following allotment:
5 1. Four Hundred Dollars ($400.00) for preparation for said
6 meeting; and
7 2. One Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($1,500.00) for the
8 regular monthly Board meeting.
9 C. D. 1. Failure of any member to attend one two Board meeting
10 meetings in any calendar year, except for justifiable excuse as
11 determined by the Chair pursuant to written policy established by
12 the Board, shall preclude the right of the member to receive his or
13 her monthly compensation established by subsection A or B of this
14 section.
15 2. In addition, any member who fails to attend two three or
16 more Board meetings in any calendar year except for extraordinary
17 circumstances as determined by the Chair pursuant to written policy
18 established by the Board shall be deemed to have committed official
19 misconduct as such term is defined by Section 93 of Title 51 of the
20 Oklahoma Statutes. To initiate a removal from office pursuant to
21 this paragraph, the Board shall pass a resolution by a majority of
22 the members of the Board detailing the alleged misconduct. Such
23 removal shall be subject to the provisions of Chapter 3 of Title 51
24 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
